CommonFields.Title: Morphology and thermo-mechanical properties of compatibilized polyimide-silica nanocomposites
Author: Al-Kandary, Sh.
Ali, A. A. M.
Ahmad, Z.
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, Kuwait University, Faculty of Science, P.O. Box 5969, Safat‐13060, State of Kuwait

Mixing.Description: 5.1086 g (0.025 mol) of ODA and 140 g of DMAc were stirred in a 250 mL conical flask at rt until a clear solution of diamine was obtained.

ChooseParameter.Other: 5.6126 g (0.025 mol) pyromellitic dianhydride (PMDA) was added to amine solution

Mixing.Description: The reaction mixture was stirred to obtain highly viscous PAA solution.

ChooseParameter.Other: APTMOS and PMDA reacted in 2:1 ratio in DMAc

Mixing.Description: PMDA and DMAc was stirred with a magnetic stirrer
1.66 mmol of APTMOS was added dropwise to mixture at rt.
0.0323 mol of TEOS was added with continued stirring

ChooseParameter.Other: The sol-gel process was carried out after adding a required amount of this mixture in the PAA solution.
